Correction: I'm still using
the neighbor's Wi-Fi.

193
00:11:22,785 --> 00:11:26,699
[LAUGHS] But, Maddie,
are you sure you're okay with this?

194
00:11:26,789 --> 00:11:28,826
Thomas Michael Wachowski,

195
00:11:28,916 --> 00:11:31,251
what did you do the entire time
I was in veterinary school?

196
00:11:31,335 --> 00:11:33,747
I worked a second job
to pay the rent and...

197
00:11:33,837 --> 00:11:35,187
A third job to pay tuition.

198
00:11:35,881 --> 00:11:39,169
You sacrificed for me.
I'm happy to sacrifice for you.

199
00:11:40,928 --> 00:11:43,135
Babe, are you sure you're okay with this?

200
00:11:44,515 --> 00:11:46,808
I mean, there's been
a Wachowski protecting this town

201
00:11:46,892 --> 00:11:48,849
for more than 50 years.

202
00:11:49,645 --> 00:11:51,261
This is a big change.

203
00:11:52,147 --> 00:11:53,637
I'm positive.

204
00:11:54,441 --> 00:11:57,277
It's time for this guy to
get out there and prove himself.

205
00:11:57,361 --> 00:12:01,229
I love Green Hills, but, you know,
I want to help people in real trouble.

206
00:12:01,323 --> 00:12:04,532
I want someone to turn to me
in a life-and-death situation

207
00:12:04,618 --> 00:12:05,983
and I'll be there for 'em.

208
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,195
I get it.

209
00:12:08,290 --> 00:12:11,248
-I'm so proud of you.
-Thank you.

210
00:12:11,334 --> 00:12:12,574
Mmm!

211
00:12:12,669 --> 00:12:15,129
And so it is with a heavy heart,
that I tell you all

212
00:12:15,213 --> 00:12:18,424
that I've accepted a position
at the San Francisco Police Department,

213
00:12:18,508 --> 00:12:20,215
effective immediately.

214
00:12:20,302 --> 00:12:24,091
It's gonna be tough to leave my hometown
and all my friendships.

215
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:27,172
But this is something
I feel like I need to do

216
00:12:27,809 --> 00:12:32,349
to grow... as both an officer and a man.

217
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,300
What do you think, Sergeant Sprinkles?

218
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:40,027
That wasn't so bad, right?

219
00:12:41,323 --> 00:12:43,064
Now all I got to do is

220
00:12:44,117 --> 00:12:45,717
tell everyone who isn't a donut.

221
