Safe!

244
00:14:46,867 --> 00:14:49,860
Yes! Yes, yes, yes, yes! I did it!

245
00:14:49,954 --> 00:14:52,742
Did you see that? I did it. I did it.

246
00:14:59,714 --> 00:15:02,297
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

247
00:15:05,928 --> 00:15:07,839
I really am alone.

248
00:15:08,514 --> 00:15:11,097
All alone. Forever.

249
00:15:18,399 --> 00:15:20,140
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

250
00:15:29,285 --> 00:15:30,946
[PANTING]

251
00:15:32,163 --> 00:15:33,824
[YELLS]

252
00:15:42,883 --> 00:15:44,294
[SATELLITE POWERS DOWN]

253
00:15:45,594 --> 00:15:48,757
I'm sure no one noticed that
giant blue explosion, right?

254
00:15:49,348 --> 00:15:51,259
[LINES RINGING]

255
00:15:55,354 --> 00:15:57,686
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

256
00:15:59,107 --> 00:16:00,689
-Hey, Wade.
-Hi, Tom.

257
00:16:00,776 --> 00:16:02,483
Uh, Wade here. [NERVOUS CHUCKLE]

258
00:16:02,569 --> 00:16:04,230
What is going on?

259
00:16:04,321 --> 00:16:05,780
Well, gosh, I think the power's out.

260
00:16:05,864 --> 00:16:09,653
Yeah, no dur! The lights are out.
The whole town is freaking out.

261
00:16:09,743 --> 00:16:11,734
-What should I do?
-TOM: <i>Okay, relax.</i>

262
00:16:11,828 --> 00:16:13,660
Take a deep breath, call Gil,

263
00:16:13,747 --> 00:16:16,580
see if they can locate
the downed line, then

264
00:16:16,667 --> 00:16:19,335
call Zim and see if he can
get his generator over to the Super Q

265
00:16:19,419 --> 00:16:20,712
so the food stays... fresh.

266
00:16:20,796 --> 00:16:24,539
WADE: <i>Call Zim before Gil?</i>

267
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:27,045
-<i>Call Gil... Hello?</i>
-I'll call you back.

268
00:16:27,135 --> 00:16:29,387
Wait! Hello? Was that
the end of the instructions?

269
00:16:29,471 --> 00:16:30,757
[PHONES RINGING]

270
00:16:30,847 --> 00:16:33,885
Okay, all right. Uh, you can do this.

271
00:16:33,976 --> 00:16:37,811
What was the first thing he said to do?

272
00:16:39,482 --> 00:16:41,564
Right. Relax.

273
00:16:51,786 --> 00:16:54,153
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

274
00:17:01,796 --> 00:17:03,958
Twenty minutes ago, an energy surge

275
00:17:04,048 --> 00:17:06,550
knocked out power
across the entire Pacific Northwest.

276
00:17:06,634 --> 00:17:07,624
What do we know?

277
00:17:07,719 --> 00:17:10,131
Well, our first instinct
was it was an EMP.

278
00:17:10,888 --> 00:17:13,641
But electromagnetic pulses
don't have that kind of power.

279
00:17:13,725 --> 00:17:16,308
NASA has ruled out
meteor strikes or solar flares.

280
00:17:16,394 --> 00:17:18,812
The Department of Energy says
it's not a power plant malfunction.

281
00:17:18,896 --> 00:17:21,774
Well, sounds like we're really good
at figuring out what it wasn't.

282
00:17:21,858 --> 00:17:24,145
This could be a prelude
to a larger attack.

283
00:17:24,235 --> 00:17:26,320
I'm suggesting we scramble
the Fifth and Sixth Regiment.

284
00:17:26,404 --> 00:17:27,565
No, no, no, no.

285
00:17:27,655 --> 00:17:30,193
This needs a much more sophisticated mind.

286
00:17:30,284 --> 00:17:32,070
Someone who understands technology.

287
00:17:32,161 --> 00:17:34,903
-You want to send in a lab rat?
-Not just any lab rat.

288
00:17:34,997 --> 00:17:36,487
A lab rat with teeth.

289
00:17:36,582 --> 00:17:38,750
You're not suggesting
who I think you're suggesting.

290
00:17:38,834 --> 00:17:40,585
-I know, he's a little weird.
-Weird?

291
00:17:40,669 --> 00:17:43,206
-No. No way.
-He's a psychological tire fire!

292
00:17:43,297 --> 00:17:46,710
But he's also brilliant.
Five PhDs, IQ off the charts.

293
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,462
And his drone tech is revolutionary!

294
00:17:49,553 --> 00:17:51,419
You're sure he can handle this?

295
00:17:51,513 --> 00:17:53,424
He has a perfect operations record.

296
00:17:53,515 --> 00:17:55,426
-Remember the coup in Pakistan?
-No.

297
00:17:55,517 --> 00:17:56,977
Or the uprising in Azerbaijanistan?

298
00:17:57,061 --> 00:17:59,143
-That's not even a country.
-Exactly.

299
00:17:59,229 --> 00:18:01,436
And you can thank Robotnik for that.

300
00:18:01,523 --> 00:18:04,641
I can't believe you're
bringing that freak into this.

301
00:18:04,735 --> 00:18:07,067
Neither can I, but

302
00:18:07,988 --> 00:18:09,103
we have no choice.

303
00:18:09,823 --> 00:18:11,780
[HELICOPTERS WHIRRING]

304
00:18:16,664 --> 00:18:19,122
[INDISTINCT SHOUTS]

305
00:18:20,542 --> 00:18:24,252
[TRUCK RUMBLING]

306
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:35,923
What the...

307
00:18:36,017 --> 00:18:38,725
[AIR HISSING]

308
00:18:58,039 --> 00:18:59,404
Are you in charge here?

309
00:18:59,499 --> 00:19:00,660
-Yes, I am...
-Nope!

310
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:01,660
-My...
-Wrong!

311
00:19:01,751 --> 00:19:03,082
-Name...
-I'm in charge!

312
00:19:03,169 --> 00:19:04,500
-Is Major...
-Me!

313
00:19:04,587 --> 00:19:06,669
-Ben...
-[WHISPERS] I'm in charge.

314
00:19:08,007 --> 00:19:10,157
You've never seen
anything like this before.

315
00:19:10,510 --> 00:19:14,720
It says I'm the top banana
in a world full of hungry little monkeys.

316
00:19:14,806 --> 00:19:17,174
Allow me to clarify. [MAKES SERVO NOISE]

317
00:19:17,268 --> 00:19:19,936
In a sequentially ranked hierarchy
based on level of critical importance,

318
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:22,147
the disparity between us
is too vast to quantify.

319
00:19:22,231 --> 00:19:24,518
-Agent Stone?
-The Doctor thinks you're basic.

320
00:19:24,608 --> 00:19:26,690
I'm initiating a sweep sequence.

321
00:19:26,777 --> 00:19:29,360
Ten miles in every direction
should suffice.

322
00:19:29,447 --> 00:19:30,983
[WHIRRING]

323
00:19:31,073 --> 00:19:33,033
-Is he still looking at me funny?
-Yes, he is.

324
00:19:33,117 --> 00:19:34,826
Tell him to stop
or I'll pull up his search history.

325
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:36,620
If you don't stop looking at the Doctor,

326
00:19:36,704 --> 00:19:38,372
-he'll take a closer look...
-I'm not deaf.

327
00:19:38,456 --> 00:19:39,998
And tell him his men report to me now.

328
00:19:40,082 --> 00:19:41,447
Blah-blah-blah.

329
00:19:41,542 --> 00:19:44,204
Excuse me? Listen, pal,
I don't know if you realize...

330
00:19:44,295 --> 00:19:46,129
I'm sorry, Major. What was your name?

331
00:19:46,213 --> 00:19:48,750
-Benning...
-Nobody cares!

332
00:19:48,841 --> 00:19:52,334
Nobody cares. Listen, Major Nobody Cares.

333
00:19:52,428 --> 00:19:54,721
[WHISPERING] You know why
nobody cares who you are?

334
00:19:54,805 --> 00:19:57,182
Because nobody cares about
your feeble accomplishments.

335
00:19:57,266 --> 00:20:00,133
And nobody cares how proud your mommy is

336
00:20:00,227 --> 00:20:02,719
that you're now reading
at a third-grade level.

337
00:20:02,813 --> 00:20:05,020
-Mmm.
-Have you finished <i>Charlotte's Web</i> yet?

338
00:20:05,107 --> 00:20:07,348
Spoiler alert: She dies in the end.

339
00:20:07,443 --> 00:20:09,480
But she leaves a big creepy egg sac.

340
00:20:09,570 --> 00:20:11,061
[MACHINERY CLICKS, WHIRRING]

341
00:20:11,156 --> 00:20:14,069
Ah... my babies.

342
00:20:14,159 --> 00:20:17,151
Whoo! Look what came out of my egg sac.

343
00:20:17,245 --> 00:20:19,327
You know what I love about machines?

344
00:20:20,081 --> 00:20:23,619
They do what they're told.
They follow their programming.

345
00:20:23,710 --> 00:20:27,060
They don't need time off to get drunk
and put the boat in the water.

346
00:20:27,798 --> 00:20:29,630
Now you do what you're told.

347
00:20:29,716 --> 00:20:32,424
Stand over there on the edge
of your personal abyss,

348
00:20:33,428 --> 00:20:35,510
and watch my machines do your job.

349
00:20:38,266 --> 00:20:40,724
-Can you feel it, Stone?
-I can feel it, Doctor.

350
00:20:41,394 --> 00:20:44,011
-It's evolution, Stone.
-[DRONES WHIRRING]

351
00:20:44,105 --> 00:20:45,436
It's evolution!

352
00:20:57,369 --> 00:20:59,781
[DRONE HUMMING]

353
00:21:01,623 --> 00:21:03,739
[BEEPING]

354
00:21:21,477 --> 00:21:23,593
-Agent Stone?
-Doctor.

355
00:21:23,688 --> 00:21:25,738
Do you see anything useful in this image?

356
00:21:26,858 --> 00:21:29,600
-Nothing at all, Doctor.
-Of course you don't.

357
00:21:29,694 --> 00:21:31,570
Your eyes weren't
expertly trained to spot tracks

358
00:21:31,654 --> 00:21:34,237
by the Native American Shadow Wolves.

359
00:21:34,323 --> 00:21:36,690
[BEEPING]

360
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:45,323
That's extraordinary.

361
00:21:45,418 --> 00:21:50,208
No. What's extraordinary is,
I've determined the exact height, weight

362
00:21:50,298 --> 00:21:51,840
and spinal curvature of this creature,

363
00:21:51,924 --> 00:21:54,416
and my computer
can't find a single match for it

364
00:21:54,510 --> 00:21:57,047
anywhere in Earth's animal kingdom.

365
00:21:58,140 --> 00:22:02,634
This blackout was not a terrorist attack,
and that's no baby bigfoot.

366
00:22:02,728 --> 00:22:06,221
This guy is something else

367
00:22:07,482 --> 00:22:09,268
entirely.

368
00:22:09,359 --> 00:22:12,101
Divert all search units
to the site of the footprint.

369
00:22:13,071 --> 00:22:15,563
That's one small step for man,

370
00:22:15,657 --> 00:22:17,944
one giant leap for me.

371
00:22:20,579 --> 00:22:22,820
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

372
00:22:22,915 --> 00:22:27,000
-[MEN CHATTERING]
-[DOGS BARKING]

373
00:22:29,212 --> 00:22:31,203
Okay, okay, everything is fine.

374
00:22:31,298 --> 00:22:33,383
You played some baseball,
got a little upset,

375
00:22:33,467 --> 00:22:36,617
lightning shot out of your butt,
and now they're coming for you.

376
00:22:37,804 --> 00:22:39,597
All right, all right.
Earth isn't safe anymore.

377
00:22:39,681 --> 00:22:41,592
Time for plan B. Mushroomville.

378
00:22:41,683 --> 00:22:44,471
But I gotta take my stuff.
Okay, essential items only.

379
00:22:44,561 --> 00:22:46,896
Okay, toothbrush, toothpaste,
hair gel, night-light.

380
00:22:46,980 --> 00:22:49,017
Funny hat. This half-eaten cantaloupe.

381
00:22:49,107 --> 00:22:50,973
Oh, and my scented candle.

382
00:22:51,068 --> 00:22:53,153
My entire comic book collection.
Bean bag chair.

383
00:22:53,237 --> 00:22:54,822
Can a bean bag chair fit in a backpack?

384
00:22:54,906 --> 00:22:56,740
No, no, no. Of course not. That's stupid.

385
00:22:56,824 --> 00:23:00,613
Okay, what else? The rings!
The rings, yes, of course.

386
00:23:01,871 --> 00:23:03,282
Here we go. Ring time.

387
00:23:03,373 --> 00:23:05,831
-Mushroom planet, here I come.
-[DRONES WHIRRING]

388
00:23:05,917 --> 00:23:07,251
Oh, no. They're right outside.

389
00:23:07,335 --> 00:23:10,077
-I gotta go somewhere else.
-[DOGS BARKING]

390
00:23:13,716 --> 00:23:15,377
Goodbye, cave.

391
00:23:16,803 --> 00:23:19,420
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

392
00:23:19,514 --> 00:23:21,175
-Hey.
-MADDIE: <i>Hey.</i>

393
00:23:21,265 --> 00:23:22,255
Whatcha doing?

394
00:23:22,350 --> 00:23:24,842
Just coloring with Jojo and Rachel.

395
00:23:24,936 --> 00:23:27,018
Ah, that sounds... half-fun.

396
00:23:27,105 --> 00:23:29,273
Hey, exciting stuff here.
We had a power outage.

397
00:23:29,357 --> 00:23:31,223
The whole town went dark.

398
00:23:31,317 --> 00:23:33,652
It was like a sign telling me
to get out of Dodge.

399
00:23:33,736 --> 00:23:35,773
-Wade must have lost his mind.
-<i>Yeah.</i>

400
00:23:35,863 --> 00:23:38,275
And he does not have much to lose.

401
00:23:38,366 --> 00:23:40,993
How's your sister?
Did she convince you to leave me yet?

402
00:23:41,077 --> 00:23:44,320
No, but she did tell me
to check your phone for dating apps.

403
00:23:44,414 --> 00:23:46,499
<i>The only apps on my phone
are the ones that came with it.</i>

404
00:23:46,583 --> 00:23:48,540
-And the Olive Garden.
-MADDIE: <i>Ah.</i>

405
00:23:48,627 --> 00:23:50,337
-Because when you're there...
-You're family.

406
00:23:50,421 --> 00:23:52,378
[GARBAGE CANS CLATTER]

407
00:23:52,798 --> 00:23:54,084
No way.

408
00:23:56,677 --> 00:23:57,963
The raccoons are back.

409
00:23:58,053 --> 00:23:59,919
And they are in for a surprise.

410
00:24:00,014 --> 00:24:02,426
Your surprise better not be
my tranquilizer gun.

411
00:24:02,516 --> 00:24:03,516
They're just hungry.

412
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,262
<i>And also, that's for bears.</i>

413
00:24:07,354 --> 00:24:09,345
-Good. Now I know it'll work.
-<i>Tom!</i>

414
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:11,566
I'm kidding. I'm just gonna
use it to scare 'em.

415
00:24:11,650 --> 00:24:12,890
Possibly to death.

416
00:24:12,985 --> 00:24:14,435
-<i>Love you, honey, bye!</i>
-Tom...

417
00:24:19,033 --> 00:24:21,274
D-I-V-O-R-C-E.

418
00:24:23,746 --> 00:24:24,986
Okay, I'm in.

419
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:27,742
With minimal damage
to Donut Lord's property.

420
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:29,828
Here we go.

421
00:24:29,918 --> 00:24:31,419
It didn't work out on Earth,
but that's okay.

422
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:32,796
You're going to a safe world.

423
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:35,372
A nice, safe world full of mushrooms.

424
00:24:35,466 --> 00:24:38,629
Mushrooms that'll be your only friends.

425
00:24:38,719 --> 00:24:40,631
That sounds awful. I can't do this.

426
00:24:40,722 --> 00:24:42,822
You have to do it.
There's no other option.

427
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:45,849
[EXHALES] All right.

428
00:24:47,604 --> 00:24:49,811
SFPD, pending background check.

429
00:24:49,898 --> 00:24:51,388
Paws in the air!

430
00:24:53,151 --> 00:24:55,768
Uh, meow?

431
00:24:55,862 --> 00:24:57,068
[SCREAMS]

432
00:24:57,155 --> 00:24:59,362
[SCREAMING]

433
00:25:01,076 --> 00:25:02,362
Ow!

434
00:25:04,204 --> 00:25:07,322
"San... Francisco?"

435
00:25:15,924 --> 00:25:17,039
[GUN CLATTERS]

436
00:25:19,803 --> 00:25:21,464
[MOANS]

437
00:25:29,479 --> 00:25:31,971
No. [GROANS]

438
00:25:35,528 --> 00:25:37,064
What?

439
00:25:57,716 --> 00:25:58,831
[SCOFFS]

440
00:25:59,468 --> 00:26:01,129
The blue devil.

441
00:26:14,316 --> 00:26:16,523
-Donut Lord?
-It can talk.

442
00:26:17,194 --> 00:26:19,654
You're not...
You're not here to abduct me, are you?

443
00:26:19,738 --> 00:26:21,149
You abducted me.

444
00:26:22,741 --> 00:26:24,903
Okay, that's a fair point. What are you?

445
00:26:24,994 --> 00:26:26,827
Why are you hiding out in my garage?

446
00:26:26,913 --> 00:26:28,244
I needed somewhere safe.

447
00:26:28,331 --> 00:26:30,708
And you're the only person
I could think of, Donut Lord.

448
00:26:30,792 --> 00:26:32,085
Why do you keep calling me Donut Lord?

449
00:26:32,169 --> 00:26:35,505
'Cause you talk to donuts.
And then eat them if they get out of line.

450
00:26:35,589 --> 00:26:36,875
Again, fair.

451
00:26:36,965 --> 00:26:38,341
Wait, wait, wait.
Where are all the mushrooms?

452
00:26:38,425 --> 00:26:39,967
Why am I still on Earth? What is...

453
00:26:40,051 --> 00:26:42,759
Oh, no! I lost my rings.

454
00:26:42,846 --> 00:26:44,132
What?

455
00:26:44,222 --> 00:26:45,883
[LOW RUMBLING]

456
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:52,432
What's happening?
Is this your mother ship?

457
00:26:53,356 --> 00:26:54,732
I'm not in the mood to get probed.

458
00:26:54,816 --> 00:26:57,524
You think you're worried?
I'm not even wearing pants.

459
00:27:01,072 --> 00:27:03,279
-What the...
-[BRAKES HISSING]

460
00:27:03,366 --> 00:27:04,447
[YELLS]

461
00:27:04,993 --> 00:27:06,410
-They're coming for me!
-Who's coming for you?

462
00:27:06,494 --> 00:27:07,495
What's that got to do with me?

463
00:27:07,579 --> 00:27:09,455
I don't have time to explain,
but you have to help me.

464
00:27:09,539 --> 00:27:11,621
No, I don't. Why?

465
00:27:11,708 --> 00:27:15,201
Well, my legs, which normally
would be classified as lethal weapons,

466
00:27:15,295 --> 00:27:16,410
feel like spaghetti.

467
00:27:16,504 --> 00:27:19,292
I need your help. Please.
It's life or death.

468
00:27:25,264 --> 00:27:26,595
[SIGHS]

469
00:27:27,266 --> 00:27:28,802
Fine. Come with me.

470
00:27:31,687 --> 00:27:33,678
Uh, little help?

471
00:27:41,530 --> 00:27:43,020
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

472
00:27:44,992 --> 00:27:46,903
All right, stay here. And be quiet.

473
00:27:46,994 --> 00:27:49,746
Good plan. Great plan!
We're already working so well together.

474
00:27:49,830 --> 00:27:52,030
Practically finishing
each other's sentences.

475
00:27:53,584 --> 00:27:54,790
Okay, bye.

476
00:27:58,214 --> 00:27:59,500
TOM: Hello there!

477
00:28:00,383 --> 00:28:01,498
Can I help you?

478
00:28:05,304 --> 00:28:06,760
Good morning, my rural chum.

479
00:28:08,182 --> 00:28:11,766
I'm... from the power company,
investigating the blackout.

480
00:28:11,852 --> 00:28:15,190
If you don't mind, I'd like to take
a few readings inside your house?

481
00:28:15,274 --> 00:28:16,900
No kidding? You're from the power company?

482
00:28:16,984 --> 00:28:18,526
-Mmm.
-Oh, you must know my buddy Spencer.

483
00:28:18,610 --> 00:28:21,352
-We play softball together.
-Ah! Spence.

484
00:28:22,030 --> 00:28:23,441
He's a good man.

485
00:28:24,324 --> 00:28:26,986
-Yeah. Come on in!
-Great.

486
00:28:27,077 --> 00:28:28,453
Take all the readings you need.

487
00:28:28,537 --> 00:28:30,278
Except, uh

488
00:28:30,372 --> 00:28:33,416
doesn't the power company usually take
their readings from outside the house?

489
00:28:33,500 --> 00:28:36,100
That way they can check them
even if you're not home.

490
00:28:36,295 --> 00:28:38,630
Also, my buddy Spencer
works for the gas company,

491
00:28:38,714 --> 00:28:40,298
and he's more of an Ultimate Frisbee guy.

492
00:28:40,382 --> 00:28:42,999
So, you want to tell me
why you think I'm dumb enough

493
00:28:43,093 --> 00:28:44,943
to just let you walk inside my house?

494
00:28:47,639 --> 00:28:48,754
[BEEPING]

495
00:28:53,478 --> 00:28:55,810
-I'm sorry, Mister...
-Wachowski.

496
00:28:55,897 --> 00:28:57,763
But everyone calls me Tom.

497
00:28:57,858 --> 00:28:59,724
Except my dentist, he calls me Tim.

498
00:28:59,818 --> 00:29:03,363
But it's gone on for so long now
that it would be weird if I corrected him.

499
00:29:03,447 --> 00:29:05,654
Well, Tom, whose dentist calls him Tim,

500
00:29:05,741 --> 00:29:09,453
you may have noticed that this entire town
has been experiencing a power outage.

501
00:29:09,537 --> 00:29:11,574
Yep, no lights. Picked up on that.

502
00:29:11,664 --> 00:29:14,500
Twenty minutes ago, I tracked
an energy pulse with a similar signature

503
00:29:14,584 --> 00:29:16,666
to the one that caused that disruption.

504
00:29:31,601 --> 00:29:33,512
Listen, uh, Mister...

505
00:29:33,603 --> 00:29:34,968
Doctor.

506
00:29:35,063 --> 00:29:37,725
Dr. Robotnik. But my dentist calls me Rob.

507
00:29:37,815 --> 00:29:39,522
Hmm.

508
00:29:39,609 --> 00:29:42,977
Look, uh, Dr. Robotskeez.

509
00:29:43,071 --> 00:29:45,155
Um, I'm sure what you're here for
is very serious,

510
00:29:45,239 --> 00:29:46,615
but it's got nothing to do with me.

511
00:29:46,699 --> 00:29:47,992
You can ask anyone in town.

512
00:29:48,076 --> 00:29:50,033
-Everyone knows me.
-I bet they do.

513
00:29:50,119 --> 00:29:53,372
I'm sure you're hella popular
with the Jebs and Merles and Billy Bobs,

514
00:29:53,456 --> 00:29:56,039
in this glorified gas-station rest stop.

515
00:29:56,125 --> 00:29:58,252
Betcha go way back
to the days of tippin' cows

516
00:29:58,336 --> 00:30:00,247
and playin' in a jug band!

517
00:30:00,338 --> 00:30:03,127
[SPITTING]

518
00:30:03,217 --> 00:30:06,130
And maybe someday you'll achieve your goal

519
00:30:06,220 --> 00:30:08,882
of getting a Costco card
or adopting a Labradoodle.

520
00:30:08,972 --> 00:30:14,558
But the reality is, I surpassed
everything you're ever going to do

521
00:30:16,271 --> 00:30:17,432
before I was a toddler.

522
00:30:18,232 --> 00:30:21,632
I was spitting out formulas
while you were still spitting up formula.

523
00:30:21,944 --> 00:30:23,309
I was breastfed, actually.

524
00:30:23,404 --> 00:30:26,396
Nice. Rub that in my orphan face.

525
00:30:27,157 --> 00:30:28,318
Mr. Wachowski,

526
00:30:28,409 --> 00:30:33,119
are you familiar with US Code 904,
Title 10, Article 104?

527
00:30:33,914 --> 00:30:35,575
-Yeah, who isn't...
-"Anyone

528
00:30:35,666 --> 00:30:39,409
who attempts to aid an enemy
of the United States shall suffer death."

529
00:30:40,838 --> 00:30:43,375
And if I'm the one that catches you,

530
00:30:43,465 --> 00:30:44,671
it'll be even worse.

531
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,091
Worse than death?

532
00:30:48,178 --> 00:30:50,340
[DRONES WHIRRING]

533
00:30:50,431 --> 00:30:52,057
SONIC: Okay, I'm a ball,
just a normal ball.

534
00:30:52,141 --> 00:30:53,350
-I'm blending in like a ball.
-[DRONE BEEPING]

535
00:30:53,434 --> 00:30:56,896
Shh. Stop talking. No, <i>you</i> stop talking.
Be quiet, Sonic. <i>You</i> be quiet, Sonic.

536
00:30:56,980 --> 00:30:59,563
Oh, I hope they aren't
scanning me with X-rays.

537
00:30:59,649 --> 00:31:01,449
I had kind of an embarrassing lunch.

538
00:31:09,492 --> 00:31:11,911
Don't freak out.
Don't freak out. Don't freak out.

539
00:31:11,995 --> 00:31:14,445
Don't freak out.
Don't freak out. Don't freak out.

540
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:16,370
I'm freaking out!

541
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:21,209
Why don't you have
your staircase carpeted?

542
00:31:21,296 --> 00:31:23,146
-[LOUD CLATTER]
-Compared to what I...

543
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,500
-Old pipes.
-Yeah.

544
00:31:27,594 --> 00:31:29,053
Probably just the house settling.

545
00:31:29,137 --> 00:31:30,798
Nothing to see here!

546
00:31:32,056 --> 00:31:33,091
Hey!

547
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:39,849
Here's the thing.

548
00:31:41,441 --> 00:31:42,806
I'm never wrong.

549
00:31:43,568 --> 00:31:45,980
Well, first time for everything, I guess.

550
00:31:46,070 --> 00:31:47,435
Would you like some cake?

551
00:31:47,530 --> 00:31:50,784
I hear raccoons have the cleanest mouths
of any animal that routinely eats garbage.

552
00:31:50,868 --> 00:31:52,358
[CHUCKLES]

553
00:31:56,123 --> 00:31:57,534
[FLOOR CREAKS]

554
00:32:03,172 --> 00:32:04,458
Look at that.

555
00:32:05,466 --> 00:32:07,298
I was right.

556
00:32:07,384 --> 00:32:09,625
Note the lack of surprise.

557
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:11,381
Shall we try this again?

558
00:32:11,472 --> 00:32:14,965
[WHISTLING "FLIGHT OF THE VALKYRIES"]

559
00:32:21,815 --> 00:32:25,774
I'm going to give you five seconds
to tell me where it is.

560
00:32:25,861 --> 00:32:27,446
-Five...
-I don't know what you're talking about.

561
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:28,947
-Four.
-Hey, tough guy. I'm a cop,

562
00:32:29,031 --> 00:32:30,323
and you're threatening an officer.

563
00:32:30,407 --> 00:32:32,576
How can you threaten somebody
who never existed?

564
00:32:32,660 --> 00:32:34,071
Three...

565
00:32:34,161 --> 00:32:35,993
Come on! Rack your brain.

566
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:40,790
You might be able to come up with some
lame excuse to go on living, in two

567
00:32:41,794 --> 00:32:42,830
one.

568
00:32:43,672 --> 00:32:45,037
Wait! Don't hurt him!

569
00:32:45,131 --> 00:32:45,996
[SHRIEKS]

570
00:32:46,091 --> 00:32:47,297
[GRUNTS]

571
00:32:47,384 --> 00:32:49,000
[RAPID BEEPING]

572
00:32:50,595 --> 00:32:51,630
[SONIC YELPS]

573
00:32:58,937 --> 00:33:00,473
This feels excessive.

574
00:33:04,150 --> 00:33:05,265
Stay behind me.

575
00:33:18,999 --> 00:33:20,285
Hiya!

576
00:33:21,543 --> 00:33:23,705
Don't worry.
I got it right where I want it!

577
00:33:24,796 --> 00:33:26,628
[SONIC YELLING]

578
00:33:26,715 --> 00:33:30,015
Can you believe Amazon is gonna deliver
packages with these things?

579
00:33:32,512 --> 00:33:35,254
This was a horrible plan!
What was I thinking?

580
00:33:37,685 --> 00:33:39,175
I'm gonna puke!

581
00:33:41,856 --> 00:33:43,312
[SONIC MOANING]

582
00:33:43,399 --> 00:33:46,187
Come on! We gotta get out of here.

583
00:33:46,277 --> 00:33:48,188
Oh, don't tell me that's all you got!

584
00:33:48,279 --> 00:33:49,610
I'm just getting started!

585
00:33:49,697 --> 00:33:52,347
Let me know if you want to go
round two with the blue.

586
00:33:53,117 --> 00:33:55,859
-[GROANS]
-[ENGINE STARTS, REVS]

587
00:34:03,919 --> 00:34:05,956
[TIRES SCREECHING]

588
00:34:09,967 --> 00:34:11,378
[ROBOTNIK GROANS]

589
00:34:11,469 --> 00:34:13,676
Doctor! Are you okay?

590
00:34:14,221 --> 00:34:16,181
I saw a guy race out
of here and thought...

591
00:34:16,265 --> 00:34:17,972
That you should stop them?

592
00:34:19,018 --> 00:34:20,179
Open your mouth,

593
00:34:20,686 --> 00:34:22,688
and say you thought that you
should stop them.

594
00:34:22,772 --> 00:34:26,310
No, I thought that maybe I should check
to see if you were okay...

595
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:28,986
You know what's hard about being
the smartest person in the world?

596
00:34:29,070 --> 00:34:32,234
-Everyone else seems stupid.
-Stupid, yes! Way to go!

597
00:34:32,324 --> 00:34:33,439
You got that one.

598
00:34:35,160 --> 00:34:39,074
Whatever this creature is,
it's our job to secure it,

599
00:34:39,164 --> 00:34:43,078
neutralize it,
uncover the source of its power.

600
00:34:43,168 --> 00:34:44,579
And if it resists

601
00:34:45,629 --> 00:34:48,872
we take it apart... piece by piece.

602
00:34:50,467 --> 00:34:52,049
See what makes it tick.

603
00:34:53,428 --> 00:34:54,759
-Stone?
-Doctor?

604
00:34:54,846 --> 00:34:56,462
Call Optical illusions.

605
00:34:57,224 --> 00:34:58,806
Tell them I need new frames.

606
00:34:59,559 --> 00:35:00,970
They know what kind I like.

607
00:35:01,728 --> 00:35:04,060
Oh, and bring that quill.

608
00:35:05,273 --> 00:35:06,559
Yes, Doctor.

609
00:35:09,778 --> 00:35:12,611
All right, pal,
you need to start talking right now.

610
00:35:12,698 --> 00:35:15,110
Who are you? What are you?

611
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:17,817
I'm a hedgehog!
I feel like that's obvious.

612
00:35:17,911 --> 00:35:19,276
And I'm in big trouble.

613
00:35:19,371 --> 00:35:20,622
Oh, <i>you're</i> in big trouble?

614
00:35:20,706 --> 00:35:23,124
You're not the one who punched
some government weirdo back there.

615
00:35:23,208 --> 00:35:25,997
You think <i>you</i> have problems?
I lost my rings.

616
00:35:26,087 --> 00:35:27,796
-Rings? What are you talking about?
-Okay.

617
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:31,544
Rings are how all advanced cultures
travel between worlds.

618
00:35:31,634 --> 00:35:34,092
And now mine are
on top of a pointy building

619
00:35:34,178 --> 00:35:36,545
I've only ever seen
on your skintight T-shirt.

620
00:35:36,639 --> 00:35:37,549
Hey.

621
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,600
So, I'd like you to take me
to San Francisco,

622
00:35:39,684 --> 00:35:43,084
so I can get back my rings and use them
to go to the mushroom planet.

623
00:35:44,522 --> 00:35:46,513
-Mushroom planet.
-Yes!

624
00:35:47,316 --> 00:35:48,477
Right.

625
00:35:52,321 --> 00:35:54,938
-Okay, pal, out you go.
-I'm sorry, what?

626
00:35:55,032 --> 00:35:58,900
Look, this is the worst possible time
for me to get myself into trouble, okay?

627
00:35:58,995 --> 00:36:01,121
You asked me to save your life,
I saved your life.

628
00:36:01,205 --> 00:36:04,368
Now, please, go find your rings.
And your mushroom land.

629
00:36:04,459 --> 00:36:06,126
Hopefully I'm gonna wake up
in a hospital bed

630
00:36:06,210 --> 00:36:08,671
and the doctor's gonna tell me
that my colonoscopy was a big success.

631
00:36:08,755 --> 00:36:09,745
Okay? So goodbye.

632
00:36:10,423 --> 00:36:13,040
-Okay. Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

633
00:36:15,845 --> 00:36:18,807
-Why aren't you leaving?
-I don't know where San Francisco is.

634
00:36:18,891 --> 00:36:19,972
-It's west.
-West?

635
00:36:20,058 --> 00:36:21,142
Straight shot, can't miss it.

636
00:36:21,226 --> 00:36:22,341
Fine. That's cool.

637
00:36:22,436 --> 00:36:24,268
I'm totally cool saying goodbye now.

638
00:36:29,318 --> 00:36:33,562
So, as I crashed into the cold,
dark water of the Pacific,

639
00:36:33,655 --> 00:36:35,362
I realized a few things.

640
00:36:36,116 --> 00:36:38,403
A, I have no idea where I'm going.

641
00:36:38,494 --> 00:36:40,735
B, saltwater stings.

642
00:36:40,829 --> 00:36:45,118
C, I shouldn't even be on
this planet right now, but I am.

643
00:36:45,209 --> 00:36:47,075
Why? Because you shot me!

644
00:36:47,169 --> 00:36:49,080
-I know.
-You shot me!

645
00:36:49,171 --> 00:36:53,335
All right, I heard you the first time.
You don't have to pile it on. Good grief.

646
00:36:53,425 --> 00:36:56,292
I'm wet. I'm cold.

647
00:36:56,386 --> 00:36:58,252
There's a fish on my head!

648
00:36:58,347 --> 00:37:01,556
And clearly, I'm not gonna be able
to do this on my own.

649
00:37:06,271 --> 00:37:08,854
[SIGHS] All right, get in the truck.

650
00:37:08,941 --> 00:37:10,682
Really? You're gonna help me?

651
00:37:10,776 --> 00:37:13,362
I guess it is a little bit my fault
that all this is happening to you.

652
00:37:13,446 --> 00:37:16,564
Not a little bit. Entirely.
It is entirely your fault.

653
00:37:16,658 --> 00:37:18,858
Okay, it's entirely my fault.
Are you coming?

654
00:37:18,952 --> 00:37:19,987
Yes.

655
00:37:22,455 --> 00:37:23,991
Road trip! Whoop-whoop!

656
00:37:24,082 --> 00:37:25,698
[SIGHS] What am I doing?

657
00:37:27,001 --> 00:37:28,669
TOM: All right, there's
gonna be rules on this trip.

658
00:37:28,753 --> 00:37:31,586
Number one,
do exactly as I say all the time.

659
00:37:31,673 --> 00:37:33,755
-Got it?
-Got it, Donut Lord.

660
00:37:33,842 --> 00:37:35,692
Would you stop with the "Donut Lord"?

661
00:37:36,302 --> 00:37:37,884
I have a name. It's Tom.

662
00:37:38,513 --> 00:37:39,503
I'm Sonic.

663
00:37:39,597 --> 00:37:41,929
Sonic. Sonic.

664
00:37:43,351 --> 00:37:45,718
So you've been spying on us all for years.

665
00:37:45,812 --> 00:37:47,188
I mean, I wouldn't call it "spying."

666
00:37:47,272 --> 00:37:49,809
We were all just hanging out,
only I wasn't invited

667
00:37:49,899 --> 00:37:51,275
and no one knew I was there.

668
00:37:51,359 --> 00:37:53,859
I can't believe Crazy Carl
was right all this time.

669
00:37:53,945 --> 00:37:56,653
Yeah. You should call him
Super Observant Carl instead.

670
00:37:57,907 --> 00:38:00,075
-Oh, my God, stop the car right now!
-What? What?

671
00:38:00,159 --> 00:38:02,328
SONIC: "The World's Largest
Rubberband Ball"?

672
00:38:02,412 --> 00:38:04,619
-We gotta see it!
-No. No.

673
00:38:04,706 --> 00:38:07,369
No, this is not some
fun family road trip, okay?

674
00:38:07,459 --> 00:38:11,168
The government wants to dissect you
and arrest me. This is serious.

675
00:38:12,715 --> 00:38:14,331
Eh, you're right, it was lame.

676
00:38:14,425 --> 00:38:16,843
Gift shop was cool, though.
I got you a mouse pad.

677
00:38:16,927 --> 00:38:18,588
When are we gonna get there?

678
00:38:18,679 --> 00:38:20,761
We will get there when we get there.

679
00:38:39,950 --> 00:38:42,744
I'm gonna go check in with Wade,
see if he knows what's going on.

680
00:38:42,828 --> 00:38:45,320
You're gonna see Wade in that glass thing?

681
00:38:45,414 --> 00:38:47,371
What is it, a teleportation box?

682
00:38:49,126 --> 00:38:50,207
It's a pay phone.

683
00:38:50,294 --> 00:38:53,672
It's mostly for drug dealers
and fugitives from the law, which is us.

684
00:38:53,756 --> 00:38:55,382
Stay in the car.
I don't want anybody seeing you.

685
00:38:55,466 --> 00:38:57,423
[GROANS] Fine.

686
00:39:01,973 --> 00:39:04,180
[MAKES DRIVING NOISES]

687
00:39:05,894 --> 00:39:08,261
[MOTORCYCLES RUMBLING]

688
00:39:08,355 --> 00:39:09,345
Huh?

689
00:39:09,439 --> 00:39:11,555
["ALL FIRED UP" BY THE LAZYS PLAYS]

690
00:39:15,362 --> 00:39:16,978
[GASPS]

691
00:39:17,072 --> 00:39:21,022
Okay, okay. That is the coolest place
on Earth, but you have to stay in the car.

692
00:39:22,452 --> 00:39:23,863
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

693
00:39:23,954 --> 00:39:25,410
[CHEERING]

694
00:39:25,497 --> 00:39:26,953
[PANTING]

695
00:39:28,416 --> 00:39:30,373
[REVVING]

696
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:32,622
Be strong. Be strong.

697
00:39:35,632 --> 00:39:36,622
Hmm.

698
00:39:37,592 --> 00:39:39,754
[LINE RINGING]

699
00:39:39,844 --> 00:39:41,926
Hello. Green Hills Police Department.

700
00:39:42,013 --> 00:39:43,754
-Wade, it's me.
-<i>Hi.</i>

701
00:39:43,848 --> 00:39:45,141
I'm so glad that you called.

702
00:39:45,225 --> 00:39:47,887
Uh, so, some guys came in
asking some questions.

703
00:39:47,978 --> 00:39:49,639
Uh, they're a little creepy.

704
00:39:49,729 --> 00:39:52,391
Kind of reminded me of
the guys from <i>Men in Black,</i>

705
00:39:52,482 --> 00:39:55,771
but not as likable
or charming as Will Smith.

706
00:39:55,861 --> 00:39:57,154
Wait, what kind of questions?

707
00:39:57,238 --> 00:40:00,606
Um, questions about terrorism?
[NERVOUS CHUCKLE]

708
00:40:00,700 --> 00:40:03,818
I told them that
I've gone ice fishing with Tom.

709
00:40:03,911 --> 00:40:05,329
He doesn't know how to make a bomb.

710
00:40:05,413 --> 00:40:07,780
<i>He can't even make bait in the cold.</i>

711
00:40:07,873 --> 00:40:09,833
All right, Wade, listen to me.
This is really important.

712
00:40:09,917 --> 00:40:11,767
Don't tell them that we talked, okay?

713
00:40:15,006 --> 00:40:17,043
You know, I think they already know.

714
00:40:19,343 --> 00:40:21,505
-Mr. Wachowski.
-[GROANS]

715
00:40:22,013 --> 00:40:23,048
Tom.

716
00:40:23,139 --> 00:40:24,973
I want you to know
that the only other person

717
00:40:25,057 --> 00:40:28,266
who ever punched me in the face
was the school bully.

718
00:40:28,352 --> 00:40:30,896
He hit me in the cafeteria,
causing a blunt-force contusion

719
00:40:30,980 --> 00:40:33,597
to the soft tissue
surrounding my orbital bone.

720
00:40:33,691 --> 00:40:35,734
Humiliated me in front of
the entire school!

721
00:40:35,818 --> 00:40:37,486
And do you know what I did in response?

722
00:40:37,570 --> 00:40:40,697
Uh, I'm assuming that you reported him
to the principal's office

723
00:40:40,781 --> 00:40:42,658
'cause that kind of behavior
is really unacceptable.

724
00:40:42,742 --> 00:40:46,036
No. I examined the inefficiency of a world
where brawn trumped brain,

725
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:49,079
and I used technology
to resolve that inefficiency.

726
00:40:49,166 --> 00:40:52,249
The boy ate his meals
through a straw for a year.

727
00:40:52,335 --> 00:40:54,135
And I have never lost a fight again.

728
00:40:54,588 --> 00:40:55,578
Until today.

729
00:40:55,672 --> 00:40:57,333
Hey, hooray for me then, huh?

730
00:40:57,424 --> 00:41:00,259
No, because you're about to become
the bully with the straw!

731
00:41:00,343 --> 00:41:02,926
I'm coming for you, Mr. Wachowski.

732
00:41:03,013 --> 00:41:04,413
And when I catch you, I'll

733
00:41:05,015 --> 00:41:06,926
-[HANGS UP]
-Hello.

734
00:41:07,017 --> 00:41:08,098
