978
00:54:23,035 --> 00:54:25,662
You come from a great town
with great people and, by my count,

979
00:54:25,746 --> 00:54:27,657
zero bad guys trying to kill you!

980
00:54:30,126 --> 00:54:32,663
Besides, what could possibly
be more important

981
00:54:32,753 --> 00:54:34,853
than protecting the people you care about?

982
00:54:41,137 --> 00:54:43,128
-Look, I get your poi...
-Whoa!

983
00:54:43,222 --> 00:54:44,428
[TIRES SQUEAL]

984
00:54:44,515 --> 00:54:45,755
Yeah!

985
00:54:47,184 --> 00:54:49,596
[TIRES SCREECHING]

986
00:54:53,065 --> 00:54:55,056
You know what? I was wrong about you.

987
00:54:55,151 --> 00:54:56,892
You're not the Donut Lord at all.

988
00:54:56,986 --> 00:54:58,693
You're more like the Jerk Lord.

989
00:54:58,779 --> 00:55:01,146
Have you noticed the harpoon
stuck in our dash?

990
00:55:06,078 --> 00:55:08,195
-[SONIC YELLS]
-Sonic!

991
00:55:08,290 --> 00:55:09,997
I was forced from my home.

992
00:55:10,083 --> 00:55:12,210
Your home is perfect,
and you're leaving it.

993
00:55:12,294 --> 00:55:14,003
-Why would you do that?
-[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

994
00:55:14,087 --> 00:55:16,670
-Your body!
-Oh, no, not again!

995
00:55:16,757 --> 00:55:17,792
Hey! Hold on!

996
00:55:17,883 --> 00:55:19,624
-Why?
-Because I'm gonna do this.

997
00:55:19,718 --> 00:55:20,924
[REVS ENGINE]

998
00:55:21,011 --> 00:55:22,422
[YELLS]

999
00:55:31,980 --> 00:55:33,812
[TIRES SCREECH]

1000
00:55:38,487 --> 00:55:39,773
Sonic!

1001
00:55:40,864 --> 00:55:42,150
Sonic!

1002
00:55:43,867 --> 00:55:46,279
[GROANING]

1003
00:55:46,370 --> 00:55:48,782
Guess I had a bonus life.

1004
00:55:49,623 --> 00:55:50,829
[GASPS]

1005
00:55:50,916 --> 00:55:52,702
Oh, yeah, baby!

1006
00:55:52,793 --> 00:55:56,036
Sonic, one. Big Tank, zero. I'm sorry.

1007
00:55:56,129 --> 00:55:58,423
-Did we get that on camera?
-How are you not dead?

1008
00:55:58,507 --> 00:56:00,214
I have no idea.

1009
00:56:00,300 --> 00:56:02,511
-Do you see me dancing?
-Yes, I saw you dance.

1010
00:56:02,595 --> 00:56:04,051
Is that all you got?

1011
00:56:04,138 --> 00:56:06,049
No, but thank you for asking.

1012
00:56:07,433 --> 00:56:09,265
[WHIRS]

1013
00:56:09,352 --> 00:56:12,470
-Uh-oh.
-Sonic! Get back in the truck!

1014
00:56:12,563 --> 00:56:14,429
SONIC: You go. I'll catch up.

1015
00:56:18,569 --> 00:56:19,650
Ha!

1016
00:56:25,410 --> 00:56:27,697
SONIC: I think that tank just had a baby.

1017
00:56:35,003 --> 00:56:37,461
[BEEPING]

1018
00:56:40,258 --> 00:56:41,293
Incoming!

1019
00:56:43,845 --> 00:56:46,553
-BOY: It's my turn!
-You just had one. It's mine!

1020
00:56:46,639 --> 00:56:48,724
Hey, stop fighting
or I'm taking that thing away!

1021
00:56:48,808 --> 00:56:49,843
Yeah, right, Dad.

1022
00:56:49,934 --> 00:56:52,141
-[CRACKLING]
-[MOTOR DIES]

1023
00:56:53,104 --> 00:56:54,604
-[TIRES SCREECH]
-[ALL YELLING]

1024
00:56:57,693 --> 00:56:59,275
[ALL PANTING]

1025
00:57:01,739 --> 00:57:02,739
Where are you going?

1026
00:57:02,823 --> 00:57:05,565
Just drive the car.
I'll take care of this.

1027
00:57:05,659 --> 00:57:07,535
And if I don't make it, just ditch me.

1028
00:57:07,619 --> 00:57:08,859
You seem good at that.

1029
00:57:18,839 --> 00:57:20,882
<i>Hey, everyone!
Welcome back to my livestream.</i>

1030
00:57:20,966 --> 00:57:22,008
<i>Today we're destroying robots.</i>

1031
00:57:22,092 --> 00:57:23,753
Step one.

1032
00:57:27,973 --> 00:57:30,010
Yes, we did it!

1033
00:57:34,563 --> 00:57:37,180
We did not do it. Who <i>is</i> this guy?

1034
00:57:37,274 --> 00:57:39,811
Ever wonder where
your tax dollars are going?

1035
00:57:39,902 --> 00:57:40,937
My turn.

1036
00:57:41,028 --> 00:57:43,947
Here, just keep us going straight.
I put it in cruise control.

1037
00:57:44,031 --> 00:57:45,782
[CHUCKLES] I feel just like Vin Diesel.

1038
00:57:45,866 --> 00:57:47,698
"It's all about family, Tom."

1039
00:57:54,000 --> 00:57:55,911
-[GRUNTS]
-SONIC: Quick suggestion.

1040
00:57:56,002 --> 00:57:58,869
Roll up into a ball
and smash him with your body.

1041
00:58:00,131 --> 00:58:02,293
Whoa! Where'd you learn how to drive?

1042
00:58:02,383 --> 00:58:04,795
Here. In this truck.
It's happening as we speak.

1043
00:58:08,223 --> 00:58:10,099
I can't reach it. Bring him in closer.

1044
00:58:10,183 --> 00:58:12,641
-What?
-Bring it in closer! Hit the brakes.

1045
00:58:12,727 --> 00:58:13,933
Oh, you mean this one?

1046
00:58:14,020 --> 00:58:15,761
-[ENGINE REVS]
-The other brakes!

1047
00:58:15,855 --> 00:58:17,345
[TIRES SQUEAL]

1048
00:58:22,487 --> 00:58:24,979
[WARBLES, DIES]

1049
00:58:25,073 --> 00:58:27,155
Ha-ha! Whoo!

1050
00:58:28,201 --> 00:58:30,067
Oh!

1051
00:58:30,161 --> 00:58:33,449
Give me a big, fat break!

1052
00:58:38,837 --> 00:58:41,545
Aw, this one is cute. Let's keep him.

1053
00:58:42,925 --> 00:58:43,915
Aah!

1054
00:58:44,760 --> 00:58:46,125
TOM: Oh, come on!

1055
00:58:46,220 --> 00:58:48,870
SONIC: How could something
so adorable be so terrible?

1056
00:58:51,934 --> 00:58:53,534
You've got car insurance, right?

1057
00:58:54,228 --> 00:58:55,184
[BOTH YELLING]

1058
00:59:00,192 --> 00:59:01,478
Buzz off.

1059
00:59:01,569 --> 00:59:03,195
-[BEEPING]
-That doesn't sound good.

1060
00:59:03,279 --> 00:59:05,614
-No, beeping is bad. Get rid of it!
-I'm trying.

1061
00:59:05,698 --> 00:59:07,449
Throw it out the win... Throw it anywhere!

1062
00:59:07,533 --> 00:59:09,983
-I can't get it off.
-All right, I'm pulling over.

1063
00:59:11,912 --> 00:59:13,368
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

1064
00:59:13,455 --> 00:59:15,867
[SONIC GRUNTING]

1065
00:59:17,835 --> 00:59:19,621
-Did I get it?
-Nope.

1066
00:59:19,712 --> 00:59:20,793
[YELPS]

1067
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:22,336
Here. Hold still.

1068
00:59:23,591 --> 00:59:25,502
It's going, it's going...

1069
00:59:25,593 --> 00:59:27,800
-It's still here.
-[BEEPING ACCELERATES]

1070
00:59:30,222 --> 00:59:31,257
Get off me.

1071
00:59:31,724 --> 00:59:33,306
Ha-ha! Nailed it!

1072
00:59:33,934 --> 00:59:35,925
[BOTH GRUNT]

1073
00:59:42,819 --> 00:59:44,150
Sonic!

1074
00:59:51,578 --> 00:59:52,739
No, no, no, no, no.

1075
00:59:59,669 --> 01:00:03,583
Hey. Come on. You're all right.
Wake up. Wake up.

1076
01:00:05,717 --> 01:00:07,879
[PANTING]

1077
01:00:10,680 --> 01:00:12,011
Did we get 'em?

1078
01:00:12,641 --> 01:00:14,723
Oh. No, there they are.

1079
01:00:14,809 --> 01:00:17,301
They are real survivors, those two.

1080
01:00:22,484 --> 01:00:23,815
Can we have a moment?

1081
01:00:26,780 --> 01:00:28,191
Pin yourself to the wall.

1082
01:00:28,281 --> 01:00:29,521
[SIGHS]

1083
01:00:29,616 --> 01:00:31,904
You know, I won't miss you
when you're gone.

1084
01:00:31,994 --> 01:00:35,862
Human beings are unreliable and stupid,
and I care very little about them.

1085
01:00:35,957 --> 01:00:38,665
But my machines are diligent, relentless.

1086
01:00:38,751 --> 01:00:40,583
They're everything to me!

1087
01:00:42,546 --> 01:00:43,752
Huh?

1088
01:00:55,184 --> 01:00:57,016
[IN JAPANESE]

1089
01:01:00,940 --> 01:01:01,930
[YELPS]

1090
01:01:03,818 --> 01:01:04,853
Mmm?

1091
01:01:07,488 --> 01:01:09,149
[TIRES SCREECH]

1092
01:01:18,457 --> 01:01:19,947
Come on, buddy.

1093
01:01:20,042 --> 01:01:22,409
You're gonna be all right.
You'll be all right.

1094
01:01:25,674 --> 01:01:26,664
[KNOCKS ON DOOR]

1095
01:01:27,926 --> 01:01:29,132
-Is Maddie here?
-No, no.

1096
01:01:29,219 --> 01:01:30,553
-Not today. Goodbye.
-It's an emergency!

1097
01:01:30,637 --> 01:01:32,594
-Bye-bye.
-Rachel, stop! Please! Maddie!

1098
01:01:32,681 --> 01:01:34,182
Don't do this. This is important.

1099
01:01:34,266 --> 01:01:36,351
-Oh, my God! Rachel, let him in.
-I am calling the police.

1100
01:01:36,435 --> 01:01:38,645
No, I am calling the FBI.
I am calling the CIA.

1101
01:01:38,729 --> 01:01:40,521
-Stop. Don't do that.
-I am calling your mother.

1102
01:01:40,605 --> 01:01:42,273
-Okay, got it.
-Maddie, can we talk?

1103
01:01:42,357 --> 01:01:43,274
Tom, what's going on?

1104
01:01:43,358 --> 01:01:45,401
You're all over the news.
I've been trying to call you.

1105
01:01:45,485 --> 01:01:47,195
I had to ditch my phone
so they couldn't track me.

1106
01:01:47,279 --> 01:01:48,690
-Ditch his phone?
-Track you?

1107
01:01:48,780 --> 01:01:51,192
-Uncle Tommy!
-Jojo! Hey!

1108
01:01:51,283 --> 01:01:53,775
Now your niece is an accessory to treason.

1109
01:01:53,869 --> 01:01:55,370
-No, she's not.
-Would you calm down?

1110
01:01:55,454 --> 01:01:57,445
Calm down? I will not calm down!

1111
01:01:57,539 --> 01:01:59,165
-Enough.
-Yes, calm down. Stop talking.

1112
01:01:59,249 --> 01:02:01,411
No. Ozzy, please. Good to see you too.

1113
01:02:01,501 --> 01:02:04,289
Oh, little Lord Baby Jesus.

1114
01:02:04,379 --> 01:02:05,665
What is that, Tom?

1115
01:02:05,756 --> 01:02:07,131
Is that plutonium? Is it e-mails?

1116
01:02:07,215 --> 01:02:08,925
-Yes, it's plutonium.
-[OZZY GROWLS]

1117
01:02:09,009 --> 01:02:10,760
Can we please go in
the other room and talk...

1118
01:02:10,844 --> 01:02:12,050
Stop it, Ozzy. Quit it!

1119
01:02:12,137 --> 01:02:13,638
This is why I told you he was no good.

1120
01:02:13,722 --> 01:02:16,089
-MADDIE: I'm not engaging.
-No, Ozzy, quit it.

1121
01:02:16,183 --> 01:02:18,050
[BOTH ARGUING]

1122
01:02:18,144 --> 01:02:20,306
Ozzy, no! Ozzy, no!

1123
01:02:21,522 --> 01:02:23,809
-Oh, catch me, Jojo.
-[THUDS]

1124
01:02:23,900 --> 01:02:26,392
[PANTING] Oh, thank God.

1125
01:02:26,486 --> 01:02:29,695
[CHUCKLES] Can I get a glass of water?

1126
01:02:38,206 --> 01:02:39,287
[BEEPS]

1127
01:02:39,374 --> 01:02:41,624
["WHERE EVIL GROWS"
BY THE POPPY FAMILY PLAYS]

1128
01:03:01,729 --> 01:03:04,391
-[MUSIC STOPS]
-[LAB POWERS DOWN]

1129
01:03:14,493 --> 01:03:17,702
[POWERING UP]

1130
01:03:18,997 --> 01:03:19,987
[BEEPS]

1131
01:03:20,082 --> 01:03:22,790
["WHERE EVIL GROWS" RESUMES]

1132
01:03:29,883 --> 01:03:31,465
[BEEPING]

1133
01:03:33,345 --> 01:03:36,303
[WIND BLOWING]

1134
01:03:41,270 --> 01:03:42,977
[ROARING]

1135
01:04:09,132 --> 01:04:10,714
[SCREAMS]

1136
01:04:10,800 --> 01:04:14,250
I just thought you might like a latte
with steamed Austrian goat milk.

1137
01:04:14,721 --> 01:04:16,632
Who do I look like, an imbecile?

1138
01:04:16,723 --> 01:04:19,932
Of course I want a latte.
I love the way you make them!

1139
01:04:20,018 --> 01:04:21,224
[BEEPING]

1140
01:04:26,774 --> 01:04:29,106
Ready the prototype.

1141
01:04:29,194 --> 01:04:30,935
With this kind of power,

1142
01:04:31,029 --> 01:04:34,943
my machines can finally reach
their full potential.

1143
01:04:41,456 --> 01:04:43,117
TOM: He's gonna be okay, Jojo.

1144
01:04:44,417 --> 01:04:47,205
Oh, thank God. He's gonna be okay, right?

1145
01:04:47,295 --> 01:04:49,797
I'm a vet, Tom. I don't even know
what I'm looking at here.

1146
01:04:49,881 --> 01:04:51,997
He's a hedgehog. Or so he says.

1147
01:04:52,091 --> 01:04:53,752
-It talks?
-Almost constantly.

1148
01:04:54,511 --> 01:04:56,468
Okay. [CLEARS THROAT]

1149
01:04:57,096 --> 01:04:58,382
-Holy...
-What?

1150
01:04:58,473 --> 01:04:59,930
His pulse is super-fast.

1151
01:05:00,017 --> 01:05:01,852
That actually might be normal for him.

1152
01:05:01,936 --> 01:05:03,562
I don't know. You gotta help him, Maddie.

1153
01:05:03,646 --> 01:05:05,387
I don't know his physiology.

1154
01:05:05,481 --> 01:05:08,018
He doesn't seem to have any broken bones.

1155
01:05:08,108 --> 01:05:10,315
He's just really banged up.

1156
01:05:11,862 --> 01:05:14,820
Oh, look at his poor little feet.

1157
01:05:16,492 --> 01:05:17,982
[MADDIE SIGHS]

1158
01:05:18,077 --> 01:05:20,677
TOM: Hang in there, buddy.
You're gonna be all right.

1159
01:05:23,791 --> 01:05:26,453
Jojo? Untie your mother. Jojo!

1160
01:05:26,544 --> 01:05:28,626
[SWEETLY] Untie Mommy.

1161
01:05:28,712 --> 01:05:30,828
Sweetie. Jojo!

1162
01:05:34,134 --> 01:05:35,510
[QUIETLY] I have to go to the bathroom.

1163
01:05:35,594 --> 01:05:37,710
-He's gonna be okay, right?
-Uh...

1164
01:05:37,805 --> 01:05:39,905
He'll snap out of this.
He'll wake up soon?

1165
01:05:40,349 --> 01:05:41,464
Oh, smelling salts!

1166
01:05:41,559 --> 01:05:44,936
Don't you have, like, vet smelling salts,
like, for cats or parakeets or something?

1167
01:05:45,020 --> 01:05:48,433
-No. They don't make cat smelling salts.
-They should.

1168
01:05:48,524 --> 01:05:52,689
I have human smelling salts
in my human first aid kit.

1169
01:05:54,114 --> 01:05:55,320
Okay.

1170
01:05:57,325 --> 01:05:58,701
-[WHISPERS] Here we go.
-Come on, buddy.

1171
01:05:58,785 --> 01:06:00,025
Gotta go fast!

1172
01:06:02,998 --> 01:06:04,784
Whoa. Where am I? What year is it?

1173
01:06:04,874 --> 01:06:06,205
Is The Rock president?

1174
01:06:06,293 --> 01:06:07,627
Whoa, buddy, you're okay. Calm down.

1175
01:06:07,711 --> 01:06:08,917
Oh, hi, Pretzel Lady!

1176
01:06:09,004 --> 01:06:10,460
Hi.

1177
01:06:11,214 --> 01:06:12,625
-Tom?
-Yeah.

1178
01:06:12,716 --> 01:06:14,016
Can I talk to you, please?

1179
01:06:17,220 --> 01:06:19,382
Space hedgehog, stay there. Try to rest.

1180
01:06:19,472 --> 01:06:21,057
You got it. I am great at resting.

1181
01:06:21,141 --> 01:06:23,100
I rest faster than anybody.
[CONTINUES, INDISTINCT]

1182
01:06:23,184 --> 01:06:24,174
Still talking.

1183
01:06:24,269 --> 01:06:26,062
Uh, first of all, can we take a moment

1184
01:06:26,146 --> 01:06:27,855
to acknowledge how
under control I've been?

1185
01:06:27,939 --> 01:06:29,646
-Amazing.
-Didn't freak out.

1186
01:06:29,733 --> 01:06:32,065
-No.
-Totally calm.

1187
01:06:32,152 --> 01:06:34,359
-Thank you.
-Ahh.

1188
01:06:34,446 --> 01:06:36,562
Second of all... [STRAINED LAUGH]

1189
01:06:36,656 --> 01:06:39,489
What the heck is going on?
Is that thing an alien?

1190
01:06:39,576 --> 01:06:43,319
Okay, so, remember how Crazy Carl
is always going on about the blue devil?

1191
01:06:43,413 --> 01:06:44,824
The blue devil!

1192
01:06:44,914 --> 01:06:47,031
-That's him? He's real?
-Yeah.

1193
01:06:47,126 --> 01:06:49,086
What is he doing here?
What are you doing here?

1194
01:06:49,170 --> 01:06:53,585
I... kinda sorta... shot our
little blue friend with your tranq gun.

1195
01:06:53,674 --> 01:06:56,211
-No, you did not.
-I didn't mean to.

1196
01:06:56,302 --> 01:06:58,262
Okay. This is kinda hard
for me to explain.

1197
01:06:58,346 --> 01:07:00,097
And it's gonna sound a little bit crazy.

1198
01:07:00,181 --> 01:07:02,343
He has to get to
the Transamerica building,

1199
01:07:02,433 --> 01:07:03,809
and I promised I'd take him.

1200
01:07:03,893 --> 01:07:06,134
Uh-uh! Aliens?

1201
01:07:06,228 --> 01:07:08,686
Maddie, your husband's lost his mind.

1202
01:07:08,773 --> 01:07:10,773
Use this as an opportunity to leave him.

1203
01:07:10,858 --> 01:07:12,565
No one would judge you.

1204
01:07:17,490 --> 01:07:19,290
So you won't hurt your feet anymore.

1205
01:07:20,159 --> 01:07:21,820
-Really?
-Uh-huh.

1206
01:07:22,828 --> 01:07:24,678
No one's ever given me a gift before.

1207
01:07:25,665 --> 01:07:27,565
I gotta check that off my bucket list.

1208
01:07:35,883 --> 01:07:37,339
[LAUGHS]

1209
01:07:37,426 --> 01:07:39,713
-All right! Looking good!
-[JOJO GIGGLES]

1210
01:07:42,349 --> 01:07:43,589
Okay.

1211
01:07:43,684 --> 01:07:46,534
You said you wanted to help
people in real trouble, right?

1212
01:07:47,145 --> 01:07:48,521
Well, that's what you're doing.

1213
01:07:48,605 --> 01:07:52,098
Blue alien hedgehogs
still count as people. Right?

1214
01:07:52,192 --> 01:07:53,478
-I think so too.
-Yeah.

1215
01:07:53,568 --> 01:07:54,774
-I think.
-Okay.

1216
01:07:54,861 --> 01:07:57,023
I love you. Did I tell you that already?

1217
01:07:57,114 --> 01:07:58,946
I don't deserve you. You know that?

1218
01:07:59,032 --> 01:08:00,318
I know that.

1219
01:08:03,161 --> 01:08:07,371
So, you're supposed to be Tom's
best friend that he won't shut up about.

1220
01:08:07,457 --> 01:08:09,118
[PANTING]

1221
01:08:09,209 --> 01:08:10,665
Well, I don't see the appeal.

1222
01:08:11,962 --> 01:08:14,078
[LAUGHING] Stop!

1223
01:08:14,172 --> 01:08:16,379
That is very gross.

1224
01:08:17,801 --> 01:08:19,007
-Hey.
-Hey.

1225
01:08:19,094 --> 01:08:22,303
So, my truck still runs,
but it's pretty much totaled.

1226
01:08:22,389 --> 01:08:24,390
You think your sister would mind
if we borrowed her car?

1227
01:08:24,474 --> 01:08:26,056
You have got to be kidding me!

1228
01:08:27,352 --> 01:08:28,645
-She'll be fine.
-Yeah, let's do that.

1229
01:08:28,729 --> 01:08:30,015
Mm-hmm.

1230
01:08:30,105 --> 01:08:32,392
This is my house!

1231
01:08:32,482 --> 01:08:34,599
-[HORN HONKING]
-SONIC: Coming through!

1232
01:08:34,694 --> 01:08:37,686
Whoa, whoa! Now this is my turn,
and I go around you.

1233
01:08:37,780 --> 01:08:40,863
Sorry! And... perfect park.

1234
01:08:40,950 --> 01:08:43,202
-MAN: What are you, crazy?
-Is there anything you didn't hit?

1235
01:08:43,286 --> 01:08:44,993
Why did we let the alien drive?

1236
01:08:45,079 --> 01:08:48,037
Hey, I got us here.
And please, five stars.

1237
01:08:49,709 --> 01:08:53,077
-So, this is it?
-That's it. That's your pyramid.

1238
01:08:53,171 --> 01:08:55,253
SONIC: Wow, look at that thing!

1239
01:08:55,339 --> 01:08:56,500
What happens now?

1240
01:08:57,383 --> 01:09:00,000
-Oh. He's... gone.
-Yep.

1241
01:09:01,345 --> 01:09:03,845
No good. You need a special key
to get to the roof.

1242
01:09:04,766 --> 01:09:06,097
What now?

1243
01:09:06,726 --> 01:09:09,514
Time for me to abuse
the power entrusted to me.

1244
01:09:19,739 --> 01:09:20,948
We got a jumper on the roof.

1245
01:09:21,032 --> 01:09:24,326
Gotta get up there fast or we're gonna
have a human pancake on our hands.

1246
01:09:24,410 --> 01:09:26,196
You came all the way from Montana.

1247
01:09:27,413 --> 01:09:29,030
Yeah. That's how serious it is.

1248
01:09:33,921 --> 01:09:34,911
Okay.

1249
01:09:36,799 --> 01:09:38,130
You just saved a life.

1250
01:09:47,017 --> 01:09:49,600
SONIC: How much longer?
I can't breathe in here.

1251
01:09:51,772 --> 01:09:54,230
Hello? Anybody there?

1252
01:09:54,316 --> 01:09:57,058
-Do you have your child in that bag?
-No.

1253
01:09:57,820 --> 01:10:00,278
I mean, yes, it's a child,
but it's not mine.

1254
01:10:01,406 --> 01:10:02,406
It's not your child.

1255
01:10:03,075 --> 01:10:04,986
Relax. I'm a cop, okay?

1256
01:10:05,077 --> 01:10:06,536
Plus, he likes it in there,
don't you, buddy?

1257
01:10:06,620 --> 01:10:08,121
SONIC: Why would I like it in here?

1258
01:10:08,205 --> 01:10:11,038
This is worse than the dog cage
you had me in earlier.

1259
01:10:12,167 --> 01:10:14,955
-Such a kidder.
-[LAUGHS]

1260
01:10:15,045 --> 01:10:17,457
-MADDIE: Okay.
-No, I'm scared of the dark!

1261
01:10:18,090 --> 01:10:19,421
Is anybody there?

1262
01:10:29,477 --> 01:10:31,263
[COUGHING]

1263
01:10:31,354 --> 01:10:34,517
[GROANS] What were you
keeping in this bag?

1264
01:10:34,607 --> 01:10:36,143
A jar of pickled farts?

1265
01:10:36,234 --> 01:10:37,984
All right. What are we looking for?

1266
01:10:40,989 --> 01:10:42,400
-[RING CHIMES]
-This.

1267
01:10:43,241 --> 01:10:45,198
Okay. What happens now?

1268
01:10:45,285 --> 01:10:47,119
Now all I have to do
is think of where I want

1269
01:10:47,203 --> 01:10:49,330
the other end of the ring
to appear, and I throw it.

1270
01:10:49,414 --> 01:10:51,451
So that's it? We did it?

1271
01:10:51,541 --> 01:10:52,872
Yeah. We did it!

1272
01:10:53,626 --> 01:10:57,164
Hey. Sorry we didn't get to do
everything on your bucket list, pal.

1273
01:10:57,255 --> 01:10:59,963
It's okay.
I did the ones I needed the most.

1274
01:11:00,049 --> 01:11:03,417
[CHUCKLES] You two are so cute.

1275
01:11:03,511 --> 01:11:05,752
-Oh, please. What?
-We are not.

1276
01:11:05,847 --> 01:11:07,178
No. We're not cute.

1277
01:11:07,265 --> 01:11:09,934
We are a couple of loose cannons
just living by our own rules.

1278
01:11:10,018 --> 01:11:11,008
Exactly.

1279
01:11:11,102 --> 01:11:12,228
-MADDIE: Really?
-TOM: Yeah.

1280
01:11:12,312 --> 01:11:15,054
And our rules include
expressing heartfelt emotions.

1281
01:11:15,149 --> 01:11:16,560
If you say so.

1282
01:11:16,650 --> 01:11:19,062
-Okay, then.
-All right.

1283
01:11:20,279 --> 01:11:22,197
-Um, you gotta go, right?
-SONIC: Yeah, I gotta go.

1284
01:11:22,281 --> 01:11:23,532
I gotta go. We gotta go too.

1285
01:11:23,616 --> 01:11:25,198
See... All right, bye-bye.

1286
01:11:29,914 --> 01:11:31,700
Just one more thing.

1287
01:11:39,590 --> 01:11:41,672
I'm sorry I was so hard on you.

1288
01:11:44,470 --> 01:11:47,553
I know it's a tough decision
for you to leave Green Hills.

1289
01:11:47,640 --> 01:11:52,055
Walking away from something
you care about has to be painful.

1290
01:11:52,144 --> 01:11:54,244
You're not sure
you really want to go, huh?

1291
01:11:55,481 --> 01:11:58,815
I don't want to go, but I can't stay.

1292
01:11:58,901 --> 01:12:01,393
As long as I'm here,
I put everyone in danger.

1293
01:12:02,029 --> 01:12:03,519
I can't do that.

1294
01:12:04,406 --> 01:12:08,491
I just want you to know that
these last two days have been

1295
01:12:08,577 --> 01:12:11,115
the best two days of my life.

1296
01:12:14,376 --> 01:12:15,877
You know, I never thought I'd say this,

1297
01:12:15,961 --> 01:12:18,546
but I'm actually gonna miss you,
you little blue devil.

1298
01:12:18,630 --> 01:12:20,337
I'll miss you too, Donut Lord.

1299
01:12:21,383 --> 01:12:22,373
Thank you.

1300
01:12:23,051 --> 01:12:24,041
For what?

1301
01:12:25,053 --> 01:12:26,509
For saving my life.

1302
01:12:40,026 --> 01:12:42,358
[RING CHIMES, WARBLES]

1303
01:12:44,572 --> 01:12:47,360
Okay. Did someone leave
their "Find My Phone" on?

1304
01:12:48,159 --> 01:12:50,070
-[DRONES WHIRRING]
-[GASPS]

1305
01:12:55,083 --> 01:12:56,073
[GASPS]

1306
01:13:14,145 --> 01:13:16,762
Welcome to San Francisco, Mr. Wachowski.

1307
01:13:17,857 --> 01:13:19,643
Are you enjoying the clam chowder?

1308
01:13:19,734 --> 01:13:21,902
It's the government wack job
who keeps trying to kill us.

1309
01:13:21,986 --> 01:13:23,442
Unsuccessfully!

1310
01:13:23,529 --> 01:13:25,405
Nice of you to swing by
on your way to Comic-Con.

1311
01:13:25,489 --> 01:13:26,839
Yeah, what are you wearing?

1312
01:13:28,868 --> 01:13:33,203
It's a flight suit, designed to modulate
my body temperature and reduce drag.

1313
01:13:33,289 --> 01:13:34,873
Yeah, and yet you still are one.

1314
01:13:34,957 --> 01:13:36,743
Ooh-hoo! Good one.

1315
01:13:36,834 --> 01:13:38,791
You are catching fire, Thomas.

1316
01:13:38,878 --> 01:13:41,478
Oh, and speaking of heat,
I see you've taken a lover.

1317
01:13:41,797 --> 01:13:42,958
Does she have a name

1318
01:13:43,049 --> 01:13:45,461
or should we just call her
"collateral damage"?

1319
01:13:45,551 --> 01:13:46,677
TOM: Hey, watch your mouth.

1320
01:13:46,761 --> 01:13:49,137
Unless you want a little more
of what I gave you earlier?

1321
01:13:49,221 --> 01:13:50,677
I punched him in the face.

1322
01:13:50,765 --> 01:13:53,016
Oh! He punched him right in the face!
It was awesome!

1323
01:13:53,100 --> 01:13:56,013
The time for talking is over!
It's time to push buttons.

1324
01:13:56,103 --> 01:13:59,267
Your flying eggs are pretty
impressive, Mr. Eggman,

1325
01:13:59,357 --> 01:14:01,644
but let's face it, you'll never catch me.

1326
01:14:01,735 --> 01:14:03,601
Confidence!

1327
01:14:03,695 --> 01:14:05,732
A fool's substitute for intelligence.

1328
01:14:07,616 --> 01:14:11,325
[MACHINE POWERING UP]

1329
01:14:13,622 --> 01:14:15,659
-That's not good.
-Uh...

1330
01:14:15,749 --> 01:14:18,918
Sonic, I know you got the super-speed
and everything, but Maddie and I...

1331
01:14:19,002 --> 01:14:20,753
Totally defenseless?
Probably gonna get blown up?

1332
01:14:20,837 --> 01:14:22,794
Pretty much, yeah.

1333
01:14:22,881 --> 01:14:25,464
Don't worry. I know exactly what to do.

1334
01:14:27,969 --> 01:14:30,006
[BOTH SCREAMING]

1335
01:14:31,431 --> 01:14:32,921
[EXHALES]

1336
01:14:33,016 --> 01:14:35,132
I was not expecting that.

1337
01:14:35,227 --> 01:14:38,427
But I was expecting not to expect
something, so it doesn't count.

1338
01:14:42,109 --> 01:14:44,459
["CATCH ME I'M FALLING"
BY KELLY FINNIGAN PLAYS]

1339
01:14:59,127 --> 01:15:00,868
[PLAYS PERCUSSIVE MELODY]

1340
01:15:12,056 --> 01:15:14,093
-[BUZZES]
-[CRACKLING]

1341
01:15:20,690 --> 01:15:22,390
Pew, pew-pew-pew, pew-pew-pew-pew!

1342
01:15:23,401 --> 01:15:24,516
[CHARGING]

1343
01:15:26,445 --> 01:15:29,278
[SONIC GASPS] Oh! [YELLS]

1344
01:15:31,826 --> 01:15:33,408
[FAINT SCREAMING]

1345
01:15:33,494 --> 01:15:35,576
[GROANS, YELLS]

1346
01:15:35,663 --> 01:15:36,744
[BOTH SCREAMING]

1347
01:15:38,082 --> 01:15:39,368
[GRUNTS] Come on!

1348
01:15:40,126 --> 01:15:41,742
Come on, come on, come on.

1349
01:15:41,836 --> 01:15:42,951
[BOTH SCREAMING]

1350
01:15:44,089 --> 01:15:44,999
[GRUNTS]

1351
01:15:52,681 --> 01:15:53,762
[SOFT THUMP]

1352
01:15:53,849 --> 01:15:56,261
Whoa, whoa, whoa! No, no, no!

1353
01:15:56,351 --> 01:15:58,888
[GRUNTING]

1354
01:15:59,938 --> 01:16:02,225
[RINGS CLATTERING]

1355
01:16:02,816 --> 01:16:04,181
[GROANS]

1356
01:16:06,737 --> 01:16:08,148
[EXHALES]

1357
01:16:08,238 --> 01:16:09,899
Oh! Hi, Tom.

1358
01:16:09,990 --> 01:16:12,197
Glad you're here. Could use some help.

1359
01:16:12,284 --> 01:16:14,035
-Old Bessie's about to give birth.
-[SIGHS]

1360
01:16:14,119 --> 01:16:16,156
-[COW MOOS]
-Give me a minute.

1361
01:16:16,830 --> 01:16:17,945
Aah.

1362
01:16:19,249 --> 01:16:22,492
Can I give you one genius piece of advice?

1363
01:16:22,961 --> 01:16:24,577
Don't run.

1364
01:16:24,671 --> 01:16:27,003
It'll only hurt more if you do.

1365
01:16:27,090 --> 01:16:29,384
And it's bad for your joints.
They've proved it.

1366
01:16:29,468 --> 01:16:31,800
All right, Eggman. You wanna get fast?

1367
01:16:31,887 --> 01:16:33,048
Let's get fast.

1368
01:16:33,138 --> 01:16:35,049
[RINGS JINGLING]

1369
01:16:36,308 --> 01:16:37,673
The hard way it is.

1370
01:16:37,769 --> 01:16:39,555
[TURBINES HUMMING]

1371
01:16:41,522 --> 01:16:42,808
[HORNS BLARING]

1372
01:16:42,899 --> 01:16:44,230
[PANTING]

1373
01:16:55,536 --> 01:16:56,822
[LOUD GRUNT]

1374
01:16:56,913 --> 01:16:58,763
That was an illegal left, by the way.

1375
01:17:01,459 --> 01:17:03,416
SONIC: <i>So, here we are again.</i>

1376
01:17:03,503 --> 01:17:05,212
<i>We've been through so much together.</i>

1377
01:17:05,296 --> 01:17:07,882
<i>Now you understand why there's
a psychotic robot doctor</i>

1378
01:17:07,966 --> 01:17:10,207
<i>chasing a supersonic blue hedgehog.</i>

1379
01:17:10,301 --> 01:17:12,884
<i>Want to know how it ends? Yeah, me too.</i>

1380
01:17:30,613 --> 01:17:31,854
How is this possible?

1381
01:17:31,949 --> 01:17:34,031
No one's ever caught up to me before.

1382
01:17:40,249 --> 01:17:41,739
[GASPS]

1383
01:17:41,834 --> 01:17:43,666
Coming through!

1384
01:17:43,752 --> 01:17:44,742
<i>Sacrebleu!</i>

1385
01:17:45,879 --> 01:17:48,041
<i>Excusez-moi, monsieur! [CACKLES]</i>

1386
01:17:52,011 --> 01:17:54,252
Here we go. Room to open it up.

1387
01:17:56,849 --> 01:17:57,884
[GRUNTS]

1388
01:18:03,522 --> 01:18:04,762
I can't lose him!

1389
01:18:11,739 --> 01:18:13,650
[LASERS FIRING]

1390
01:18:19,079 --> 01:18:21,787
If you can't beat 'em, blind 'em.

1391
01:18:24,918 --> 01:18:26,956
Lost visual contact.

1392
01:18:32,010 --> 01:18:35,674
You're not allowed up there!
It's one of the Seven Wonders!

1393
01:18:38,475 --> 01:18:40,557
[CHARGING]

1394
01:18:40,643 --> 01:18:42,179
[PANTING]

1395
01:18:43,688 --> 01:18:44,849
[BEEPING]

1396
01:18:44,939 --> 01:18:45,895
[YELLS]

1397
01:18:48,568 --> 01:18:50,980
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]

1398
01:18:52,697 --> 01:18:54,062
[COINS JINGLE]

1399
01:18:55,658 --> 01:18:57,774
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

1400
01:18:59,996 --> 01:19:01,532
WOMAN: Get out of here!

1401
01:19:05,460 --> 01:19:07,121
[ROBOTNIK CACKLES]

1402
01:19:09,464 --> 01:19:12,707
You're an astonishing little creature.

1403
01:19:14,969 --> 01:19:17,210
It'll be fun to take you back to the lab

1404
01:19:17,305 --> 01:19:19,656
for a litany of invasive
exploratory procedures.

1405
01:19:20,518 --> 01:19:22,179
Any last words?

1406
01:19:23,145 --> 01:19:25,887
Guac. I like that word.

1407
01:19:27,691 --> 01:19:29,901
I don't have to tell you how
many scientific breakthroughs

1408
01:19:29,985 --> 01:19:32,352
have been made possible by animal testing.

1409
01:19:32,446 --> 01:19:33,530
You're being very selfish.

1410
01:19:33,614 --> 01:19:34,775
Going my way?

1411
01:19:34,865 --> 01:19:36,071
What the... [GRUNTS]

1412
01:19:36,158 --> 01:19:37,364
[ENGINES WHIRRING]

1413
01:19:37,451 --> 01:19:39,362
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1414
01:19:41,497 --> 01:19:43,454
Who the hell do you think you are?

1415
01:19:44,041 --> 01:19:45,202
[LOUD GROAN]

1416
01:19:46,794 --> 01:19:48,295
I'm the Donut Lord, you son of a...

1417
01:19:48,379 --> 01:19:49,585
[YELLS]

1418
01:19:51,799 --> 01:19:53,335
[GRUNTS]

1419
01:19:53,426 --> 01:19:55,133
Autopilot, adjust.

1420
01:19:55,886 --> 01:19:57,297
Why?

1421
01:19:57,388 --> 01:20:00,676
Why would you throw
your life away for this thing?

1422
01:20:00,766 --> 01:20:02,142
That's why I don't have friends.

1423
01:20:02,226 --> 01:20:04,311
Next thing you know,
you're somebody's best man.

1424
01:20:04,395 --> 01:20:05,896
They want to have the wedding out of town.

1425
01:20:05,980 --> 01:20:08,017
Like nobody has anything better to do!

1426
01:20:08,858 --> 01:20:10,895
-Anyway, where were we?
-[GROANS]

1427
01:20:10,985 --> 01:20:13,523
Oh, yes. You were about to die.

1428
01:20:14,197 --> 01:20:15,687
[GUNSHOT RICOCHETS]

1429
01:20:15,782 --> 01:20:17,732
That's our sheriff you're messing with.

1430
01:20:19,202 --> 01:20:21,193
-And our blue devil...
-[CHAIN SAW REVS]

1431
01:20:21,288 --> 01:20:24,497
who, as everyone can see,
is a very real creature,

1432
01:20:24,583 --> 01:20:26,995
and not at all invented by me.

1433
01:20:28,420 --> 01:20:29,535
[CHAIN SAW IDLES]

1434
01:20:29,629 --> 01:20:31,422
-Oh, careful.
-Just... Just put it away.

1435
01:20:31,506 --> 01:20:32,712
Tom?

1436
01:20:46,396 --> 01:20:48,307
I don't mean to be indelicate here,

1437
01:20:48,398 --> 01:20:51,811
but someone should get some ice,
keep the body fresh.

1438
01:20:54,821 --> 01:20:57,062
He's just a silly little alien.

1439
01:20:57,574 --> 01:20:58,985
He didn't belong here!

1440
01:21:01,203 --> 01:21:02,489
That little alien

1441
01:21:03,497 --> 01:21:06,866
knew more about being human
than you ever will.

1442
01:21:07,543 --> 01:21:08,658
His name was Sonic.

1443
01:21:09,795 --> 01:21:11,001
This was his home.

1444
01:21:12,173 --> 01:21:13,504
And he was my friend.

1445
01:21:14,425 --> 01:21:16,917
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

1446
01:21:38,783 --> 01:21:39,898
He's all yours.

1447
01:21:41,661 --> 01:21:42,861
TOM: Everyone, get back!

1448
01:21:46,582 --> 01:21:49,244
I think you have something
that belongs to me.

1449
01:21:50,044 --> 01:21:51,034
Whoa.

1450
01:21:53,214 --> 01:21:55,046
[POWERING DOWN]

1451
01:22:00,263 --> 01:22:02,130
This is my power.

1452
01:22:02,224 --> 01:22:04,807
And I'm not using it to run away anymore.

1453
01:22:04,893 --> 01:22:08,352
I'm using it to protect my friends.

1454
01:22:12,693 --> 01:22:14,855
[WEAPONS POWERING UP]

1455
01:22:21,910 --> 01:22:24,572
[WHIRRING]

1456
01:22:31,420 --> 01:22:33,002
[BEEPING]

1457
01:22:36,967 --> 01:22:38,378
[LAUNCHING]

1458
01:22:51,398 --> 01:22:52,231
[GRUNTS]

1459
01:23:04,078 --> 01:23:05,578
-[EXCLAIMING]
-[ALARMS BLARING]

1460
01:23:05,663 --> 01:23:07,779
Ooh! Now you've done it!

1461
01:23:07,874 --> 01:23:09,160
Guess what, Eggman?

1462
01:23:09,250 --> 01:23:11,787
I'm not leaving Earth. You are.

1463
01:23:12,420 --> 01:23:13,706
Donut Lord?

1464
01:23:47,038 --> 01:23:49,326
[ROBOTNIK YELLS]

1465
01:23:58,425 --> 01:24:00,666
[PEOPLE CHEERING, CLAPPING]

1466
01:24:02,805 --> 01:24:05,092
-I told you, you got this.
-Hey, <i>we</i> got this.

1467
01:24:07,101 --> 01:24:08,387
[GASPS]

1468
01:24:08,977 --> 01:24:10,217
[LAUGHING]

1469
01:24:18,070 --> 01:24:20,570
-I think these belong to you.
-Thank you very much.

1470
01:24:21,573 --> 01:24:23,199
No more pushing people off of buildings.

1471
01:24:23,283 --> 01:24:24,783
You know I can't promise that.

1472
01:24:28,622 --> 01:24:31,364
-You did pretty good, space hog.
-Thanks, Donut Lord.

1473
01:24:31,458 --> 01:24:34,576
You're gonna have to explain
this "Donut Lord" thing.

1474
01:24:34,670 --> 01:24:37,503
Nope, sorry.
That's for me and the little guy. Right?

1475
01:24:37,589 --> 01:24:39,841
We got our thing,
you got your thing with your... sister.

1476
01:24:39,925 --> 01:24:40,925
Oh, my God, my sister.

1477
01:24:41,009 --> 01:24:45,720
Gotta go fast. Gotta go fast.
Gotta go fast. Gotta go fast.

1478
01:24:45,807 --> 01:24:47,423
Jojo, put on my Fitbit,

1479
01:24:48,518 --> 01:24:50,179
so I can at least get some steps.

1480
01:24:50,270 --> 01:24:51,620
We can never go back there.

1481
01:24:53,148 --> 01:24:54,513
I mean, are we?

1482
01:24:56,735 --> 01:24:59,185
'Cause it kind of feels like
we're home right now.

1483
01:24:59,738 --> 01:25:00,773
Really?

1484
01:25:02,490 --> 01:25:06,859
I kind of feel like I checked
the "save a life" box off my bucket list.

1485
01:25:09,456 --> 01:25:13,290
Now all I want to do is spend my life
with the people I care about.

1486
01:25:14,711 --> 01:25:15,961
I want to check that box.

1487
01:25:17,297 --> 01:25:19,004
Okay, I like that.

1488
01:25:19,716 --> 01:25:22,174
All right, everybody. Nothing to see here.

1489
01:25:22,260 --> 01:25:23,341
Let's disperse.

1490
01:25:23,428 --> 01:25:25,304
Just another ordinary day in Green Hills.

1491
01:25:25,388 --> 01:25:26,938
Carl, I'll take that chain saw.

1492
01:25:27,599 --> 01:25:29,385
WADE: Come on. Let's go!

1493
01:25:29,476 --> 01:25:31,018
You act like you've never seen a fight

1494
01:25:31,102 --> 01:25:35,688
between an intergalactic space rodent
and a robot with a doctorate.

1495
01:25:44,867 --> 01:25:46,153
You got enough there?

1496
01:25:46,619 --> 01:25:48,735
-Yes, Mr. Manager.
-Need any more?

1497
01:25:48,829 --> 01:25:50,240
You get that away.

1498
01:25:53,793 --> 01:25:55,033
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1499
01:26:00,883 --> 01:26:02,294
Mr. and Mrs. Wachowski?

1500
01:26:03,511 --> 01:26:04,501
Yes?

1501
01:26:06,847 --> 01:26:08,890
A token of appreciation
from your government,

1502
01:26:08,974 --> 01:26:12,074
for keeping quiet about recent incidents,
which never occurred.

1503
01:26:13,229 --> 01:26:14,435
[BOTH LAUGH]

1504
01:26:14,522 --> 01:26:16,229
TOM: Wow!

1505
01:26:16,315 --> 01:26:18,932
-Wonder what it is.
-Money to fix the house?

1506
01:26:19,026 --> 01:26:21,267
-Letter from the President?
-You'll see.

1507
01:26:21,362 --> 01:26:22,773
Okay.

1508
01:26:25,908 --> 01:26:27,990
-Olive Garden.
-TOM: Hmm, yeah.

1509
01:26:28,077 --> 01:26:30,538
[CHUCKLES] The way you said "You'll see"
made me think

1510
01:26:30,622 --> 01:26:32,457
it was something better
than the things we said.

1511
01:26:32,541 --> 01:26:35,283
Have you tried their
Never Ending Pasta Bowl?

1512
01:26:35,377 --> 01:26:36,836
-It never ends.
-[MADDIE CHUCKLES]

1513
01:26:36,920 --> 01:26:39,207
-That sounds... fancy.
-Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

1514
01:26:39,297 --> 01:26:41,459
Well, thank you.
We appreciate the gesture.

1515
01:26:42,634 --> 01:26:45,511
Oh, hey. I guess we can close the file
on that Robotnik guy, huh?

1516
01:26:45,595 --> 01:26:46,585
Just disappeared.

1517
01:26:46,680 --> 01:26:51,220
I'm sorry, but no such person exists
or ever has existed.

1518
01:26:52,686 --> 01:26:53,892
I wish that were true.

1519
01:26:53,979 --> 01:26:55,480
You haven't by any chance been in contact

1520
01:26:55,564 --> 01:26:58,399
with a certain alien creature
since the incident, have you?

1521
01:26:58,483 --> 01:27:00,193
Uncle Sam would love
to have a chat with him.

1522
01:27:00,277 --> 01:27:02,689
Very casual. Brunch, perhaps.

1523
01:27:04,489 --> 01:27:05,615
Oh, you mean the little blue guy.

1524
01:27:05,699 --> 01:27:06,689
-Mmm.
-No.

1525
01:27:06,783 --> 01:27:08,774
-No, nothing. No.
-Mm-mmm.

1526
01:27:08,869 --> 01:27:11,169
-Doubt we'll ever hear from him again.
-Mm-mmm.

1527
01:27:11,746 --> 01:27:13,111
Very well.

1528
01:27:13,707 --> 01:27:15,118
Okay.

1529
01:27:15,208 --> 01:27:16,744
-Thank you.
-Great.

1530
01:27:16,835 --> 01:27:17,916
Mmm.

1531
01:27:18,879 --> 01:27:19,869
Yep.

1532
01:27:19,963 --> 01:27:23,332
[DOOR CREAKS]

1533
01:27:23,426 --> 01:27:25,552
To be honest,
I'm pretty pumped about the pasta bowl.

1534
01:27:25,636 --> 01:27:26,626
[CHUCKLES]

1535
01:27:26,721 --> 01:27:28,639
So, do you guys wanna
watch a movie or what?

1536
01:27:28,723 --> 01:27:30,015
Sorry, buddy, it's a school night.

1537
01:27:30,099 --> 01:27:31,558
It's time for you to go back to your cave.

1538
01:27:31,642 --> 01:27:33,758
What? It's 3:00 in the afternoon!

1539
01:27:33,853 --> 01:27:35,437
You know how you get
when you're tired. Come on.

1540
01:27:35,521 --> 01:27:37,011
Me? I'm not like anything.

1541
01:27:37,106 --> 01:27:40,315
-[GROANS] You guys are so uncool.
-Yeah, yeah, we know.

1542
01:27:40,401 --> 01:27:42,236
-[GROANS]
-Hey, buddy, where you going?

1543
01:27:42,320 --> 01:27:44,220
You said I have to go back to my cave.

1544
01:27:44,530 --> 01:27:45,691
We did.

1545
01:28:00,588 --> 01:28:03,046
Oh, my... Are you kidding me?

1546
01:28:04,550 --> 01:28:05,961
I can't believe it.

1547
01:28:06,385 --> 01:28:07,625
How did you...

1548
01:28:08,512 --> 01:28:10,594
It's... It's all here.

1549
01:28:14,393 --> 01:28:16,100
[MADDIE CHUCKLES]

1550
01:28:20,817 --> 01:28:23,354
Look at this! Are you kidding?
And the beanbag?

1551
01:28:23,445 --> 01:28:25,446
No way! [CHUCKLES]
How did you even get this?

1552
01:28:25,530 --> 01:28:28,147
And you got it all the way over...
Oh! [LAUGHS]

1553
01:28:28,241 --> 01:28:30,341
I love it, I love it,
I love it, I love it!

1554
01:28:32,955 --> 01:28:36,414
[SIGHS] Well, welcome home.

1555
01:28:36,500 --> 01:28:39,037
Thank you, so much.

1556
01:28:41,505 --> 01:28:42,870
[CHUCKLES]

1557
01:28:46,259 --> 01:28:48,045
[OZZY BARKING]

1558
01:28:48,136 --> 01:28:49,592
SONIC: <i>Oh, no, you don't.</i>

1559
01:28:49,680 --> 01:28:52,422
<i>No second-best animal friends
allowed in my room.</i>

1560
01:28:52,516 --> 01:28:54,183
-[OZZY BARKS]
-<i>Wait. What are you doing?</i>

1561
01:28:54,267 --> 01:28:56,599
<i>Stay away from me.</i> [LAUGHS] <i>Stop it!</i>

1562
01:28:56,687 --> 01:28:58,678
<i>I'm warning you. I've got nunchucks!</i>

1563
01:28:58,772 --> 01:29:01,264
<i>Hey, stop. Okay, you can stay.</i>

1564
01:29:01,358 --> 01:29:02,658
-[LAUGHING]
-[OZZY BARKING]

1565
01:29:09,825 --> 01:29:11,316
[WATER SPLASHES]

1566
01:29:18,459 --> 01:29:21,952
My grasp on sanity remains... absolute.

1567
01:29:23,715 --> 01:29:25,251
Isn't that right, Agent Stone?

1568
01:29:26,759 --> 01:29:29,626
[GRUNTING]

1569
01:29:30,471 --> 01:29:32,587
Why don't you get a head start?

1570
01:29:32,682 --> 01:29:34,593
-[LOUD GRUNT]
-[ROCK THUDDING]

1571
01:29:34,684 --> 01:29:37,676
Do some rock-connaissance. [CACKLES]

1572
01:29:37,770 --> 01:29:40,683
Rock-connaissance!
Come on! That's hilarious!

1573
01:29:40,773 --> 01:29:42,514
What's the matter with you?

1574
01:29:42,608 --> 01:29:45,817
-[BEEPS]
-Here's the "sitch." Uninhabited planet.

1575
01:29:47,405 --> 01:29:51,364
No resources, no supplies,
no apparent way home.

1576
01:29:52,368 --> 01:29:53,824
[CHUCKLES]

1577
01:29:53,911 --> 01:29:55,493
A lesser man would die here.

1578
01:29:57,373 --> 01:29:58,704
[QUILL BUZZING]

1579
01:29:58,791 --> 01:30:00,452
I'll be home by Christmas.

1580
01:30:03,629 --> 01:30:07,373
[MAKING SERVO NOISES]

1581
01:30:13,891 --> 01:30:16,098
[GRUNTS]

1582
01:30:18,145 --> 01:30:20,011
[YELLS]

1583
01:30:20,105 --> 01:30:22,016
Rock-connaissance!

1584
01:30:22,608 --> 01:30:25,100
[LOUD CACKLING]

1585
01:30:25,194 --> 01:30:27,105
Come on! Cheer up!

1586
01:30:27,946 --> 01:30:30,608
["SPEED ME UP" PLAYS]

1587
01:32:26,066 --> 01:32:29,024
[BEEPING]

1588
01:32:29,111 --> 01:32:31,569
If these readings are accurate, he's here.

1589
01:32:31,655 --> 01:32:32,941
I found him.

1590
01:32:33,032 --> 01:32:34,818
I just hope I'm not too late.

1591
01:32:36,785 --> 01:32:37,820
[GRUNTS]

1592
01:32:45,879 --> 01:32:49,042
["SPEED ME UP" PLAYS]

